video.title: Sesame Street: Classics
video.synopsis: Relive your favorite moments from the beloved staple of children's programming with this collection of classic "Sesame Street" scenes and sketches.

episodes.synopsis: Gordon introduces Sesame Street's residents -- both Muppet and human -- and Cookie Monster disrupts Kermit the frog's lecture on the letter "W."
episodes.title: The First Sesame Street

episodes.synopsis: An orange Oscar demands a baked-bean sundae, and Kermit the frog explains the word "in." Solomon Grundy and Wanda the witch make their debut.
episodes.title: An Orange Grouch and a Green Grover

episodes.synopsis: Bert and Ernie star in "Banana Telephone," Oscar calls "Dial-a-Grouch," and Bob sings "Who Are the People in Your Neighborhood?"
episodes.title: Kermit Croons Being Green

episodes.synopsis: A prank pulled on Bert backfires, Cookie Monster's call to his mother ends when he eats the telephone, and Susan sings "One of These Things."
episodes.title: Here Comes Cookie Monster

episodes.synopsis: Comedian-pianist Victor Borge demonstrates musical notes, Madeline Kahn sings "Me, Me, Me," and Ernie is fooled by a paper boy.
episodes.title: Naming Barkley

episodes.synopsis: Telly Monster moves to Sesame Street, Cookie is "Casey McFee," Kermit reports for "Sesame Street News" and the Count sings.
episodes.title: Telly Monster Moves In

episodes.synopsis: Grover serves up burgers, Bert and Ernie ransack their own apartment, and Biff helps Salvador DaDa create a museum.
episodes.title: Grover the Waiter at Your Service

episodes.synopsis: Guy Smiley and Cookie Monster appear in "Beat the Time”; Grover sings about the letter “I”; and Herry Monster visits the eye doctor.
episodes.title: Disco Snuffy and Big Bird

episodes.synopsis: Bobby McFerrin sings the ABCs; Kermit the frog reports on London fog; and Placido Flamingo performs the “Lost Toy Opera.”
episodes.title: Bobby McFerrin Sings the Alphabet

episodes.synopsis: An early Elmo learns "hello" in sign language, Phil Harmonic and Placido Flamingo perform live from the Nestropolitan Opera, and baby turtles swim.
episodes.title: Early Elmo

episodes.synopsis: Lena Horne sings a duet with Grover, Kermit reports for "Sesame Street News," Ernie brings home a surprise, and a girl makes a storybook.
episodes.title: Lena Horne Sings with Grover

episodes.synopsis: Guy Smiley goes on safari and scares the animals, the Two-Headed Monster sings a lullaby to itself, and Mumford's magic trick shrinks David.
episodes.title: Guy Smiley on Safari

episodes.synopsis: Beloved funnyman Bill Cosby visits the gang and perform the "Alphabet Song," while Bert and Ernie show that it's possible to share cookies.
episodes.title: Bill Cosby Sings!

episodes.synopsis: As winter comes to Sesame Street, Grover decides to visit his buddy Kermit, while Kermit himself interviews the legendary Three Little Pigs.
episodes.title: A Sesame Winter Wonderland

episodes.synopsis: When Ernie's sandwich goes missing, Sherlock Hemlock is quick to investigate, while kids get a lesson in crossing streets safely.
episodes.title: Sherlock Hemlock Investigates

episodes.synopsis: Lena Horne delights the gang with the much-loved "Alphabet Song," while Bob puts a new spin on an old tale with the story of Cutie and the Beast.
episodes.title: Lena Horne Sings the Alphabet Song

episodes.synopsis: Kermit warbles out a tune called "This Frog" in this collection and the Two-Headed Monster and Oscar's girlfriend, Grundgetta, visit the Street.
episodes.title: Kermit Sings!

episodes.synopsis: Election Day comes to Sesame Street and Big Bird is eager to make his voice heard, while Grover dazzles with his performance of "ABC Disco."
episodes.title: Get Out and Vote

episodes.synopsis: When Snuffy starts sneezing, Big Bird recommends a checkup and Dr. Thad and the Medications are on hand to perform "The 10 Commandments of Health."
episodes.title: The Ten Commandments of Health

episodes.synopsis: The lovable and eccentric Cookie Monster pretends to be a bunny, but no one's sure why, while Wanda the Witch takes a bewitching look at the letter W.
episodes.title: Cookie Monster in Disguise

episodes.synopsis: Country crooner Johnny Cash visits the Street to sing a truly tall tale, and Alistair Cookie presents a showing of "Little House on the Prairie."
episodes.title: Legendary Country Star Johnny Cash Sings a Tall Tale

episodes.synopsis: Wanda the Word Fairy comes to the Street to share some interesting words, and Bert is determined to uncover the identity of the park tuba player.
episodes.title: Welcome Wanda the Word Fairy

episodes.synopsis: Telly and the Grand High Triangle Lover marvel at the wonders of triangles, and Bert and Ernie discuss the difference between "loud" and "quiet."
episodes.title: All Hail the Grand High Triangle Lover

episodes.synopsis: In this high-energy collection, Ruth Buzzi visits the Street and joins Big Bird in a special dance, while strong winds pose a problem for Grover.
episodes.title: Dance 'Til You Drop!
